    <annotation>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>{ Semper Occasio statim arripienda. Multa cadu[n]t inter Calicem,
                    supremaq[ue] Labra.</marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref person="Erasmus" book_title="Adagia" language="LA" text="Multa cadunt inter Calicem, supremaque Labra"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <language ident="IT">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Chi ha Tempo, non aspetti Tempo.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Qui non est hodi&egrave;, cras min&ugrave;s aptus erit.</marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref person="Ovid" book_title="Remedia Amoris" language="LA" text="Qui non est hodi&egrave;, cras min&ugrave;s aptus erit."/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The opportunity must always be seized at once. "Many things fall between the cup and the lip." Whoever has time, do not await time [Don't put off until tomorrow
            what you can do today]. "He who is not [ready] today, will be less ready tomorrow."</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Reru[m] omniu[m] preciosissima Pra[e]da,
                        occasio. Semper tibi pendeat hamus. Marius, nullis Repulsis excursus: Etiam Virescit Vulnere Virtus. <!--JG: Quote from the poet Aulus Furius Antias, whose writing only have survived when cited in other works -->.
                    Aliquo modo expugnat[u]r, quod undiq[ue] Inuaditur.</marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Gaius Marius"/>
                    <X-ref person="Ovid" book_title="Ars amatoria" language="LA" text=" Semper tibi pendeat hamus."/>
                    <X-ref person="Aulus Furius Antias" book_title="Unknown" language="LA" text="Etiam Virescit Vulnere Virtus"/>
                    <X-ref person="Jerome" book_title="Unknown" language="LA" text="Aliquo modo expugnatur, quod undique inuaditur."/> <!--JG: Appears in Matteo Gribaldi's De methodo ac ratione studendi libri tres (p. 53), who attributes is to Jerome; https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=b1PbpCLGUJYC&pg=PT97&lpg=PT97&dq=Aliquo+modo+expugnatur&source=bl&ots=tHvClet2fg&sig=s3FH_dHJBzL6W0w5ympl5_HkI4s&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qDuJVeadCsbdUdWvjFg&ved=0CC4Q6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=Aliquo%20modo%20expugnatur&f=false-->
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Opportunity is the most valuable loot of all things. "Have your hook always baited."
            Marius,  running out without restraints: "indeed, courage grows strong at a wound." "What is invaded from every side, is conquered in any way."</translation> 
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>General, &amp; special</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Instructions, annexed to [the]</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>pr[a]emisses, as more matter of commendable Exploits, &amp; worthy Strategems.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
